Police Minister Bheki Cele says ministers in the Justice Cluster will meet on Tuesday to address the recent killings on the Cape Flats.   Cele met with the community of Philippi East on Monday after six women were gunned down in the Marcus Garvey informal settlement in Philippi East on Friday while five others were killed in separate incidents on Saturday. Two people were also killed in Hanover Park. The police minister says plans on how to address the issue will be discussed during the meeting. “We have meeting of the Justice Cluster where all the ministers will be there. From there we will come with a road map of a quick implementation not just [in] Philippi but in the broader metro trying to stop the murders that are taking place here,” explains Cele. Click below for related video…. 